      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 32
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "This 2002 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) is a mechanically sorted example of the marque\u2019s water-cooled evolution. At its heart is the 3.6L M96 flat-six engine, utilizing VarioCam Plus for optimized valve timing and lift, delivering a linear power curve and sharp throttle response. The 6-speed longitudinal manual gearbox provides tactile, short-throw engagement, while the rear-wheel-drive configuration ensures pure steering feedback uncorrupted by torque steer. Significant preventative maintenance has been performed, including an IMS bearing retrofit and a fresh rear main seal (RMS), mitigating common platform vulnerabilities. The chassis remains taut, with the multi-link rear suspension and MacPherson strut front end maintaining factory-spec geometry for precise turn-in and high-speed stability. While the aesthetics show the honest patina of a well-loved driver's car, the drivetrain and structural rigidity remain uncompromisingly sharp for the enthusiast seeking a visceral driving experience.",
      "price": 34500.0,
